===============================================================================
###############################################################################

Revision 217:
* display feeds with empty folders better
* fix uninstall to clean up man pages and translation files
* rewrote man pages to be more useful
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Revision 216:
* Add enhanced status for downloading podcasts.
Add printing for podcast queuing to awaiting threads, and download
progress from curl downloads. All status prints are now thread
safe so the messages are not intermingled. Added -s option to
tuxcast to enable this printing. This can be used in combination
with tuxstatus (see: http://github.com/kookjr/tuxstatus).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Revision 215:
* Allow exclusion of certain podcast episodes.
Some podcast feeds have more than one type of episode. Added the
ability to apply exclusion patterns that when matched that episode
will be treated like it is downloaded, but it will not be. Currently
the patterns are case sensitive strings. Added a -p to the -u option
of tuxcast-config to add patterns. All versions of feed display also
display the patterns.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Revision 214:
* Added formatted printout for feeds in tuxcast-config -G.
Each feed is printed on one line, with the feed name, dir (id) and
feed. The columns are constant width and dynamically calculated.
The feed dir to id mapping is printed before the feeds. To minimize
the changes, I overloaded the feed::displayConfig method so other
places it is called can still have the original format.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Revision 213:
* Define SUBVERSION_REVISION dynamically so you don't have to remember to change version.h each commit.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

